<Placemark><name>Red Lake Reservation</name><description><![CDATA[<h3>Red Lake Reservation</h3><p><b>&#9888; Tribal overflight assertion (20,000 ft):</b> Tribal resolution prohibits flights below 20,000 ft over Red Lake lands. Not on FAA sectionals; not FAA-enforced. Cited by Red Lake Nation to impound a 1946 Stinson 108 that made a safe engine-out emergency landing on a reservation road on 15 October 2025 (Smedsmo); aircraft still impounded as of March 2026 while the legal dispute continues. AOPA has requested federal intervention. <i>(See navdata PDF. Not FAA-enforced.)</i></p><p><b>Nearest airports:</b> <b>3G2</b> 21 NM &middot; <b>04MN</b> 21 NM &middot; <b>KVWU</b> 26 NM</p><p><b>Type:</b> Federal American Indian Reservation &nbsp; <b>States:</b> MN &nbsp; <b>Area:</b> 882 sq mi</p><p><b>Pop (2020):</b> 5,448 &nbsp; <b>Housing:</b> 1,485</p><p><i>Full overflight considerations: navdata/Overflight_Considerations.pdf</i></p>]]></description><Style><IconStyle><scale>1.1</scale><Icon><href>http://maps.google.com/mapfiles/kml/paddle/red-circle.png</href></Icon></IconStyle><LabelStyle><scale>0.9</scale></LabelStyle></Style><Point><coordinates>-95.16315,48.14312,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
