<Placemark><name>Hualapai Indian Reservation</name><description><![CDATA[<h3>Hualapai Indian Reservation</h3><p><b>&#9888; Tribal overflight assertion (15,000 ft):</b> Hualapai Tribe asserted authority over airspace up to 15,000 ft AGL after a 2009 paraglider landing incident. Dispute settled before codified case law emerged. Commercial air tour activity over Hualapai lands is separately regulated under 14 CFR 93 Subpart U (Grand Canyon SFRA). <i>(See navdata PDF. Not FAA-enforced.)</i></p><p><b>Nearest airports:</b> <b>3AZ5</b> 6 NM &middot; <b>KL37</b> 8 NM &middot; <b>52AZ</b> 9 NM</p><p><b>Type:</b> Tribal Designated Statistical Area &nbsp; <b>States:</b> AZ &nbsp; <b>Area:</b> 1,591 sq mi</p><p><b>Pop (2020):</b> 1,738 &nbsp; <b>Housing:</b> 473</p><p><i>Full overflight considerations: navdata/Overflight_Considerations.pdf</i></p>]]></description><Style><IconStyle><scale>1.1</scale><Icon><href>http://maps.google.com/mapfiles/kml/paddle/red-circle.png</href></Icon></IconStyle><LabelStyle><scale>0.9</scale></LabelStyle></Style><Point><coordinates>-113.40101,35.50950,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
